EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to housing; authorizing the governing body of a city or county in
certain regions to impose, under certain circumstances, a linkage fee on
certain developers to pay for certain expenses related to the
development of affordable housing; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes the governing body of a city or county to regulate and restrict the
2 improvement of land, taking into account the availability of and need for affordable housing
3 in the community. (NRS 278.020) Existing law further requires the governing bodies of
4 certain cities and counties to: (1) ensure an adequate supply of affordable housing when
5 implementing a master plan; (2) adopt certain measures to maintain and develop affordable
6 housing to carry out the housing plan required in the master plan; and (3) report certain
7 information relating to affordable housing to certain entities. (NRS 278.230, 278.235,
8 278.237) Existing law also authorizes the governing body of a city or county to adopt zoning
9 regulations that, in relevant part, ensure the development of an adequate supply of affordable
10 housing in the community. In exercising such power, the governing body of the city or county
11 is authorized to use any controls relating to land use or principles of zoning that the governing
12 body determines to be appropriate, including, without limitation, density bonuses,
13 inclusionary zoning and minimum density zoning. (NRS 278.250)
14 Existing law creates the Tahoe Regional Planning Agency as part of the Tahoe Regional
15 Planning Compact and sets forth certain provisions regarding the governance of the Lake
16 Tahoe region by the Agency, including provisions relating to the creation, review and
17 amendment of a regional plan. (NRS 277.200)
18 Section 1 of this bill authorizes, under certain circumstances, the governing body of a city
19 or county which is located within any region governed by a regional planning agency created
20 by interstate compact (currently the Lake Tahoe region) to impose a linkage fee [on the
21 development of residential units in the city or county which are 1,000 square feet or more] if

