22 the regional plan adopted by such a regional planning agency [: (1)] calls for the development
23 of affordable housing in the region [;] and [(2)] identifies the use of linkage fees and deed
24 restrictions as tools for the development of affordable housing [.] on the: (1) development of
25 any residential units in the city or county which are 1,000 square feet or more; (2)
26 construction of any addition to existing residential units which are 750 square feet or
27 more; and (3) remodeling of any residential units if the value of the remodeling is
28 estimated to be more than $100,000. Section 1 further: (1) requires such fees to be used for
29 the purpose of paying certain fees to assist in the development of affordable housing units of a
30 certain size which must be not more than 1,000 square feet per unit and subject to a deed
31 restriction that requires the units to be sold or rented as affordable housing; and (2) prohibits
32 such fees from being imposed on the development of residential units for affordable housing
33 [.] and certain construction or remodeling relating to accessory dwelling units that are or
34 will be subject to a deed restriction that requires the units to be sold or rented as
35 affordable housing. Section 2 of this bill applies the definitions in existing law relating to
36 planning and zoning, including the definition for “affordable housing,” to the provisions of
37 section 1. Section 4 of this bill provides that the powers granted by section 1 are subordinate
38 to the powers of a regional planning agency created by interstate compact. Section 3 of this
39 bill applies certain provisions relating to judicial relief from or review of any final action,
40 decisions or order of a governing body to an action or proceeding which arises from the
41 provisions of section 1.
