1 Section 1. Chapter 278 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection [3,] 4, if, in any region of this
4 State for which there has been created by interstate compact a regional planning
5 agency, the regional plan adopted by the regional planning agency calls for the
6 development of affordable housing in the region and identifies the use of linkage
7 fees and deed restrictions as tools for the development of such affordable
8 housing, the governing body of a city or county located within the region that is
9 governed by the regional planning agency may impose a linkage fee on the
10 [development] :
11 (a) Development of any residential units in the city or county which are
12 1,000 square feet or more ;
13 (b) Construction of any addition to any existing residential units which are
14 750 square feet or more; or
15 (c) Remodeling of any existing residential units if the value of the
16 remodeling is estimated to be more than $100,000,
17  to assist in the development of affordable housing that the governing body
18 determines will be necessary as a result of the development [of the residential
19 units.] , construction or remodeling, as applicable.
20 2. The determination of the governing body required pursuant to subsection
21 1 must be based on a finding that there is an essential nexus between the new
22 development [of residential units] , construction or remodeling, as applicable,
23 and the need for affordable housing.
24 [2.] 3. The linkage fee imposed pursuant to subsection 1 must be:
25 (a) Roughly proportional in nature and extent to the impact of the proposed
26 new development [of residential units;] , construction or remodeling, as
27 applicable;
28 (b) Used to assist in the development of affordable housing which must be:
29 (1) Not more than 1,000 square feet per unit of affordable housing; and

